   About HVO

           Directions to the Hawaiian Volcano Observatory (HVO)

                         Map of Island of Hawai`i
   Map of Island of Hawai`i. The US Geological Survey's Hawaiian Volcano
   Observatory (USGS, HVO) is located within the Hawai`i Volcanoes
   National Park, denoted by the green area.

   From Hilo to HVO: Take Highway 11 to just beyond the 28-mile marker,
   then take the left turn lane to the entrance of Hawai`i Volcanoes
   National Park. From the Entrance Station, follow Crater Rim Drive
   (highlighted yellow on bottom map) for two miles to the Hawaiian
   Volcano Observatory (HVO).

   From Kailua-Kona to HVO: Take Highway 11 for 95 miles to just beyond
   the 29-mile marker, then turn right to the entrance of Hawai`i
   Volcanoes National Park. Service Entrance Station. From the Entrance
   Station, follow Crater Rim Drive (highlighted yellow on bottom map) for
   two miles to the Hawaiian Volcano Observatory (HVO).

   Kilauea summit area

   For a printable map in PDF, visit the National Park Service's website
   at http://www.nps.gov/havo/ and click on 'maps'. skip past bottom
   navigational bar
